OL,3,COne of the British Isles' oldest
OL,4,Cdrummers dies aged 102
OL,6,FJersey man Alfred 'Honky' Hall,
OL,7,Fbelieved to be one of the oldest
OL,8,Fdrummers in the British Isles, has
OL,9,Fdied at the age of 102.
OL,11,FHe started playing as a child, saving
OL,12,Fup to buy an old drum for #5 from a
OL,13,Fpawn shop that was across the road
OL,14,Ffrom his house.
OL,16,FAlfred could not afford drumsticks so
OL,17,Fmade his own from old chair parts at
OL,18,Fthe rubbish tip and used biscuit tins
OL,19,Fto create his first full drum kit.
